Simon Mitchell stole from Donna's Dream House, a charity for terminally ill children in Blackpool . 
  The 44-year-old volunteer worker admitted stealing a laptop and TomTom satnav from the charity . 
  He claimed to have close celebrity contacts to gain the trust of the organisation . 
  Mitchell was meant to be raising the profile of the charity after a devastating arson attack in 2011 . 
  He pleaded guilty to two counts of theft at Preston Crown Court . 
 